8615.name: The Void
description: You are suspended in cool electric space above a translucent plain.  You feel
synesthesia invading your nerves and reshuffling your senses.  The sky is the
same obsidian color as the ground and you can't find a horizon.
You see machine dreams and taste violet phosphor.
You see a large dance hall.

8630.name: Road to Newfane
description: You are on a gently curving north-south road.  On your east side a youthful
river sparkles blue and rushes in the sunlight.  On the west, green leaves and
green ferns burst against the rich brown earth.  You feel the heat of your
healthy muscles as you travel swiftly down the well-paved road.
You may recall now if you like.
You see a village square.
You see machine dreams and taste violet phosphor.

8632.name: A Large Dance Hall
description: You are inside a large dance hall with a very polished, very slippery wooden
floor.  You see three long lines of dancers, alternating men and women, in
some sort of progressive country dance.  Two fiddlers, a flautist, and a
harpsichord player provide the music.  You hear scattered screams of joy
from the dancers.
You may recall now if you like.
You see machine dreams and taste violet phosphor.
The dancers have been here all night and intend to dance until dawn.

8634.name: A Small Hall
description: You are inside a small hall with a rough wooden floor.  You see dozens of
people in the hall chasing one poor man who is yelling at the top of
his lungs.  Wait a minute.  These people are all holding hands and smiling!
The man in front is leading them in a spiral!  They're DANCING!  And you
thought people didn't dance like this any more!
You may recall now if you like.
You see machine dreams and taste violet phosphor.

8640.name: The Forest Near Newfane
description: You walk into a dark forest near the village of Newfane.  All
around you ancient oak trees stand, blocking all light.  The forest is
dark, and a heavy mist floats over the ground.  The forest is dead
quiet, not a single sound, not even the leaves blowing.  You feel like
you are lost.

8648.name: The Newfane General Store
description: You walk into the Newfane General Store.  The walls all around you
are stocked full of items for sale, mostly things that you need on a
daily bases.  The shopkeeper smiles are you as you walk into the small
shop, customers are somewhat rare in these parts.

8639.name: Yule Tree Farm
description: This is the Yule Tree Farm at the top of Mountain Road.  All around you,
young Yule Trees saturate your senses with dark green needles and pine
essence.
You see a mountain ridge against the sky.

8636.name: Road by a Pond
description: You are passing by a large pond, almost a small lake.  You notice a small
wooden shack by the side of the road.
You may recall now if you like.
You see a wooden church set back among the trees.
You see machine dreams and taste violet phosphor.
The shack looks hand-made by an amateur.

8638.name: Mountain Road
description: You are following a road at the top of a mountain ridge with sky all around
you.  Distant valleys are spread out below you on both sides.  There are
many horsemen and horsewomen on this road, riding hell-for-leather out of
sheer exhilaration.  You wish you had a horse!
You may recall now if you like.
You see several acres of thickly planted, very young Yule Trees.
You see machine dreams and taste violet phosphor.

8645.name: Before The Portal
description: Before you stand a large portal, almost a rip in time.  Before you,
you can see a small village, in a lush, green world.  The portal
ripples in the middle of the forest here, and awaits someone to enter
it.  A large rock with the symbol of Ragnarok on it, stands next to
the portal.

8631.name: Newfane Village Square
description: You are on the lawn of the village square of Newfane, resting
against an oak after your vigorous journey.  The late spring breeze
feels warm and sensuous on your body.  An Ale is in progress: you spy
more than a dozen fiddlers and hundreds of Morris Dancers dressed in
white cotton and wearing colorful hats and bells.
You see the Road to Newfane.

8646.name: The Newfane Pub
description: You walk into a small pub in the village of Newfane.  You see the
pub is old, the oak walls surround you, dressed with paintings and
trophies.  The pub is somewhat dark, but full of Newfane Citizens, who
look like farmers.  To the north you see the bar, stretching across
the whole pub, which has a few open seats.

8637.name: An Old Wooden Church
description: As you enter the hall, you see the largest crowd of people you've ever seen in
your life.  They're also the noisiest crowd you've ever heard, and as they
press around you, the SWEATIEST crowd you've ever felt!  At the front of the
hall, a group of musicians are playing 'Chorus Jig'.
You see a road by a pond.

8647.name: The Village Council Hall
description: You walk into a small building on the northside of the village.
This place is known as the Village Council Hall.  Before you stands a
large open building, row of benches line most of the floor, except for
the raised floor to the north.  There a podium stands infront of the
whole building, looking over the row of chairs.  A large religious
symbol hangs on the wall behind the podium, which somewhat says this
place is also a church of some sorts.

8631.name: The Mayor Of Newfane~
description:
He stands tall, and old, he is the Mayor of Newfane, a small
village lost to the winds of The Void.  The origance of Newfane is
unknown, it just floats within the void.  The mayor looks at you and
smiles.
